text.tspan: In this section, we will describe the necessary steps
required for the correct system execution.
It is possible to skip this setup, if the user already
has a database created and accessible with the bolt
protocol. In this case skip to step 3. in order to
start the DB (*note that when running the application
the contents of the database will be modified/erased).
Once the application is open, create a new project,
Click New, in the project list (fig1)
Select “Create Local Database” and insert Database
Finally, start the database by clicking “Start”. When
it’s running, it should have a green color
